HEADWORD: Maidan
<hw>Mai*dan"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>midan</asp>, <asp>meidan</asp>, <asp>mydan</asp>, etc.]</altsp>
<ety>[Hind. & Per. <ets>maid⟦amac⟧n</ets>, fr. Ar.
<ets>maid⟦amac⟧n</ets>.]</ety> <def>In various parts of Asia, an open
space, as for military exercises, or for a market place; an open grassy
tract; an esplanade.</def></p>

<p><q>A gallop on the green <qex>maidan</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Crawford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maiden</ent>⟦br⟧
